options.content: AWS Elemental MediaTailor

AWS Elemental MediaTailor is a content personalization and monetization service that implements high-quality, server-side ad insertion and channel assembly.

For more information on configuring this integration, please visit our documentation.

panels.description: The number of ads for which MediaTailor bills customers based on insertion.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, value['count'] AS "Ads Billed Count"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'AdsBilled'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Ads Billed

panels.description:
The number of times that the ADS pointed at an ad that wasn't yet transcoded by the internal transcoder service in the time period that you specified.

A high value for this metric might contribute to a low overall Avail.FillRate.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, value['count'] AS "Ad Not Ready Count"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'AdNotReady'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Ads Not Ready

panels.description: The number of errors received while MediaTailor was generating manifests in the CloudWatch time period that you specified.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, value['sum'] AS "Manifest Errors"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'GetManifest.Errors'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Manifest Errors

panels.description:
The number of non-HTTP 200 status code responses and timed-out responses that MediaTailor received from the origin server in the CloudWatch time period that you specified.

All origin.* metrics are emitted for requests that are fulfilled directly from the origin. They are not emitted for cached origin responses.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp, value['Sum'] AS "Origin.Errors"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'Origin.Errors'
  AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Origin Errors

panels.description:
Avail.Duration

The planned total number of milliseconds of ad avails within the CloudWatch time period. The planned total is based on the ad avail durations in the origin manifest.

Avail.FilledDuration

The planned number of milliseconds of ad avail time that MediaTailor will fill with ads within the CloudWatch time period.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  multiIf(metric_name = 'Avail.Duration', 'Avail Duration',
          metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedDuration', 'Avail Observed Duration',
          metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedFilledDuration', 'Avail Observed Filled Duration',
          metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedSlateDuration', 'Avail Observed Slate Duration',
          NULL) AS "Metric Description",
  (value['sum']) AS "Value"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE (metric_name = 'Avail.Duration' 
  OR metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedDuration'
  OR metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedFilledDuration'
  OR metric_name = 'Avail.ObservedSlateDuration')
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.title: Avail Durations

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  splitByChar('.', assumeNotNull(metric_name))[2] AS "Skipped Reason",
  value['sum'] AS "value"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE startsWith(metric_name, 'Skipped')
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.description: This metric is an indicator of the health of the input. If the value isn't stable, investigate determine if there are problems with your source, and/or problems in the network between MediaLive and the upstream system.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  metric_name,
  multiIf(metric_name = 'GetManifest.Latency', 'Manifest Latency', metric_name = 'AdDecisionServer.Latency', 'ADS Latency', NULL) AS "Metric Description",
  (value['sum'] / value['count']) AS "Latency"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE (metric_name = 'AdDecisionServer.Latency' OR metric_name = 'GetManifest.Latency')
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.title: Manifest Latency / ADS Latency

panels.description:
The simple average of the rates at which the responses from the ADS filled the corresponding individual ad avails for the time period that you specified.

To get the weighted average, calculate the AdDecisionServer.Duration as a percentage of the Avail.Duration. For more information about simple and weighted averages, see Simple and weighted averages.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  metric_name,
  (value['sum'] / value['count']) AS "Ad Decision Server FillRate"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'AdDecisionServer.FillRate'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.title: Ad Decision Server FillRate

panels.description: The number of non-HTTP 200 status code responses, empty responses, and timed-out responses that MediaTailor received from the ADS within the CloudWatch time period that you specified.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  metric_name,
  value['sum'] AS "Ad Decision Server Errors"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'AdDecisionServer.Errors'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.title: Ad Decision Server Errors

panels.description: The number of timed-out requests to the ADS in the CloudWatch time period that you specified.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  metric_name,
  (value['sum'] / value['count']) AS "Ad Decision Server Timeouts"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'AdDecisionServer.Timeouts'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC, metric_name ASC

panels.title: Ad Decision Server Timeouts

panels.description:
The file size of the origin manifest in bytes for both HLS and DASH. Typically this metric is used in conjunction with Origin.ManifestFileSizeTooLarge.

All origin.* metrics are emitted for requests that are fulfilled directly from the origin. They are not emitted for cached origin responses.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp,
  value['sum'] AS "Manifest File Size Bytes"
FROM
  ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakTableMetrics}
WHERE metric_name = 'Origin.ManifestFileSizeBytes'
AND account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
AND labels['ConfigurationName'] = '${v_MediaLive_ConfigurationName}'
AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC

panels.title: Manifest File Size

panels.title: Manifest Errors

targets.rawSql:
SELECT timestamp, concat(level, ' - ', origin_id, ' - ', event_type, ' - ', cause), level, origin_id, event_type, cause
FROM ${v_TrafficPeakProject}.${v_TrafficPeakManifestLogs}
WHERE 
  account_id = '${v_AWS_AccountId}'
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
